---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="ai in coding" description="Thread on using AI in coding — not for speed, but for changed outcomes">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-4">
      <a href="/writing" class="text-spice hover:underline">writing</a> <span class="text-faint">/</span> ai-coding
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-normal animate-fade-up">ai in coding</h1>

    <div class="space-y-10 mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">1/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">been using ai more in coding lately</p>
        <p>not chasing speed</p>
        <p>more like trying to see where it actually changes outcomes</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">2/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">first thing that stood out:</p>
        <p>tools don't fail loudly</p>
        <p>they fail quietly when intent is unclear</p>
        <p class="text-dim mt-3">that's where most cost hides</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">3/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">starting with code feels productive</p>
        <p>until it isn't</p>
        <p>starting with structure feels slow</p>
        <p>until it compounds</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">4/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">dumping the mess early helps</p>
        <p class="text-dim">what is this supposed to do</p>
        <p class="text-dim">who uses it</p>
        <p class="text-dim">what happens when no one's paying attention</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">5/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">this part isn't about ai</p>
        <p>it's about being honest about the game being played</p>
        <p class="mt-3">bad games still ship</p>
        <p class="text-dim">they just collect interest later</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">6/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">ai is useful here</p>
        <p>not as a brain</p>
        <p>but as something that keeps poking at weak spots</p>
        <p class="text-dim">lazy users</p>
        <p class="text-dim">weird incentives</p>
        <p class="text-dim">edge behavior</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">7/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">once the shape is clear</p>
        <p>code gets boring in a good way</p>
        <p>translation instead of guessing</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-dim">fewer "works but feels wrong" moments</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">8/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">a quiet pattern shows up across systems</p>
        <p>most failures aren't technical</p>
        <p>they're decisions made vague on purpose</p>
        <p class="text-dim">or left unpaid for too long</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">9/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">loop that seems to hold:</p>
        <p class="text-spice">build → see what broke → update beliefs → cut</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-dim">skipping the belief update just ships the same mistake faster</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thread-post">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">10/</span>
        <p class="mt-2">ai doesn't give taste or judgment</p>
        <p>those still come from scars</p>
        <p>but it removes places to hide from unclear thinking</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-dim">that alone changes the slope</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/writing" class="text-spice hover:underline">← back to writing</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .thread-post {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(212, 168, 100, 0.12);
  }

  .thread-post p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
